ed partly cloudy to cloudy skies with prospects of thunderstorms and rains over some parts of the region during the afternoon/evening hours. It predicted that the region is expected to have day and night temperatures of 30 to 34 degree Celsius and 20 to 25 degree Celsius respectively. Vanguard News Nigeria. The Nigerian Meteorological Agency ( NiMet) has predicted sunny and hazy weather conditions over the northern region with few chances of thunderstorms over some parts of the southern states for Monday. NiMet’s weather outlook on Sunday in Abuja also predicted day and night temperatures to be from 34 degree Celsius… November 3, 2019 In "News" The Nigerian Meteorological Agency (NiMet) has predicted cloudy and sunny, hot dry weather conditions with chances of thunderstorms over most parts of the country on Saturday. November 2, 2018 In "News" The Nigerian Meteorological Agency (NiMet) has predicted partly cloudy conditions over the central states of the country on Monday with thundery showers over Jalingo and Ibi in the afternoon and evening. April 16, 2017 In "News"